You play a casual roguelike based on pachinko / peggle? This is the game for you!

BUT

If yo're seeking a robust and a solid gameplay experience, then it's a no, because:
1 - There is too much RNG in the game;
2 - A lack of working builds / synergies that actually work, so you will lose a lot of runs. And the worst is, your build may be able to steamroll all game, but the final boss will simply counter everything your build do.
3 - I started playing the game in 2023 so I didn't catch a lot of nerfs / fixes and whatnot, but a quick skim over reddit has a lot and I mean a lot of complaints over problems with the devs trying to nerf whats too strong;
4 - You depend far too much on your balls bouncing a lot. If you shoot badly you can kiss your run goodbye;
5 - 80% of orbs are terrible and don't work very well;
6 - Combat mechanics are awful in a sense that if you don't pick up a pierce orb or splash orb you won't scale fast enought at later stages;
7 - You don't get incentives for getting into normal fights because you gain nothing but gold and paid orb upgrades or healing. Always run from combat to shop, chest or question mark.

This game is very fun in the beggining but it has a lot of glaring issues. 90% of relics are garbage or uninspiring, 80% of orbs are garbage, a lot of tilesets are terrible. Hopefully devs won't abandon cuz the game just left early acess...


It may sound as a salty Andy review after losing a good run, but no.
